headline: A Look at CMS Energy’s Valuation Following Its Latest Dividend Announcement
summary: CMS Energy (CMS) shares were higher Tuesday after the utility announced a quarterly dividend of 49 cents per share. This marks the latest in a series of regular dividend payments for investors and underscores the company’s steady capital return program. See our latest analysis for CMS Energy. CMS Energy has been quietly building momentum, with a 12.49% year-to-date share price return and a 14.12% total shareholder return over the past year.
